{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4fbfe0a8-0a51-4b0d-80b0-71e71bf30805","content":"### 3. Create the GitHub environment\n\nIn your repo settings → **Environments** → create an environment named **`nuget`**. You can optionally add protection rules (e.g., require approval).\n\n---\n\n**How it works:** With trusted publishing, `dotnet nuget push` uses the OIDC token (granted by `id-token: write`) to authenticate — no API key needed. NuGet verifies the token came from your registered repo/workflow/environment.\n\n**To publish:** push a tag like `git tag v1.0.0 && git push origin v1.0.0`.\n\nThe workflow is at `.github/workflows/publish.yml`. Want me to adjust anything (e.g., different trigger, .NET version, or multi-TFM)?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"96123cec-1e30-4bb4-be26-ae6f2ab4a50c","outputTokens":174,"requestId":"B812:3B700E:C7F4C1:E65F05:69F2A847"},"id":"ef46a098-9b87-408b-a6e2-c6d2db6d39b8","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:54:37.948Z","parentId":"b144f8ac-626a-4bad-aeff-55fe068c9e5c"}
